Package general

Interface PECI<E extends EventI>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - event that necessarily implements the interface EventI
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    PEC
    public interface PECI<E extends EventI>
    A container that provides operations made to a collection (it can be any kind of collection) of event classes that implement the interface EventI.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method Description
      void addEvent​(E event)
      Appends the specified event to the container.
      void clear()
      Removes all of the events from the container.
      E getEvent()
      Returns the next event in the same way as in the method nextEvent(), but does not remove it from container.
      boolean isEmpty()
      Returns true if this list contains no events, and false otherwise.
      E nextEvent()
      Retrieves and removes the next event in the container.
      void removeEvent​(E event)
      If the event is present in the container, it removes occurrences of the specified event.

    • Method Detail

      • addEvent

        void addEvent​(E event)
        Appends the specified event to the container.

        There may exist limitations on adding some events to the container, depending on the type of collection used.

        Parameters:
        event - - event to be added to the container

      • nextEvent

        E nextEvent()
        Retrieves and removes the next event in the container. The order of removal depends on the type of collection used
        Returns:
        next event in the container.

      • removeEvent

        void removeEvent​(E event)
        If the event is present in the container, it removes occurrences of the specified event. If the event is not present, an error message should be issued.
        Parameters:
        event - - event to be removed from the event container

      • getEvent

        E getEvent()
        Returns the next event in the same way as in the method nextEvent(), but does not remove it from container.
        Returns:
        next event in the container

      • clear

        void clear()
        Removes all of the events from the container. The container will be empty after this call returns.

      • isEmpty

        boolean isEmpty()
        Returns true if this list contains no events, and false otherwise.
        Returns:
        true if this list contains no events, and false otherwise
